com.jimmoores.quandl

Class QuandlSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jimmoores.quandl.QuandlSession

  • public final class QuandlSession
extends Object
    Quandl session class. Create an instance with either 
       QuandlSession.of(SessionOptions.withAuthToken(AUTH_TOKEN));
    to use your API authorization token string, or use the API without a token, which may have lower rate/volume limits. 
       QuandlSession.of();
    Then call one of the methods to fetch data!

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static QuandlSession create(String authToken)
        Create a Quandl session to use a specific authorization token (authToken) with all requests. Using a token means you can make more requests. Note that this method does not check the quandl.auth.token property. Creating this object does not make any actual API requests, the token is used in subsequent requests.
        Parameters:
        authToken - a Quandl API authorization token
        Returns:
        an instance of the Quandl session with an embedded authorization token

      • create

        public static QuandlSession create()
        Create a Quandl session without an authorization token (authToken). An attempt will be made to read the java property quandl.auth.token and use that if available. Any resulting SecurityException is logged at debug level, otherwise it is ignored and no auth token is used. Using a token means you can make more requests. Note creating this object does not make any actual API requests, the token is used in subsequent requests.
        Returns:
        an instance of the Quandl session, not null.

      • create

        public static QuandlSession create(SessionOptions sessionOptions)
        Create a Quandl session with detailed SessionOptions. No attempt will be made to read the java property quandl.auth.token even if available. Note creating this object does not make any actual API requests, the token is used in subsequent requests.
        Parameters:
        sessionOptions - a user created SessionOptions instance, not null
        Returns:
        an instance of the Quandl session, not null

      • getMultipleHeaderDefinition

        public Map<String,HeaderDefinition> getMultipleHeaderDefinition(MultiMetaDataRequest request)
        Get header definitions from Quandl about a range of quandlCodes returned as a Map of Quandl code to HeaderDefinition. The keys of the map will retain the order of the request and are backed by an unmodifiable LinkedHashMap. Throws a QuandlRuntimeException if it can't find a parsable quandl code or Date column in the result.
        Parameters:
        request - the request object containing details of what is required, not null
        Returns:
        an unmodifiable Map of Quandl codes to MetaDataResult for each code, keys ordered according to request, not null
